    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-peanut-curry-with-crispy-fried-tofu/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Drain your <strong>tofu</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper, then cut the <strong>tofu</strong> into strips</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-peanut-curry-with-crispy-fried-tofu/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and roughly chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>tofu strips </strong>and <strong>garam masala </strong>to the pan and cook for 5-6 min, turning occasionally until golden and crisp</p><p>Meanwhile, heat a separate, large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-peanut-curry-with-crispy-fried-tofu/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped pepper </strong>and<strong> shallot wedges </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>with your <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>and <strong>curry powder </strong>and cook for 2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>and <strong>gluten free</strong> <strong>soy sauce </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-peanut-curry-with-crispy-fried-tofu/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong>, <strong>coconut stock </strong>and <strong>peanut butter </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 3 min or until the sauce has slightly thickened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-peanut-curry-with-crispy-fried-tofu/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the sauce is thickening, squeeze your pouch[es] of <strong>cooked white long grain rice</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>(just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-peanut-curry-with-crispy-fried-tofu/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While everything's cooking, chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-peanut-curry-with-crispy-fried-tofu/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>coconut peanut curry </strong>over the<strong> cooked rice</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>crispy fried tofu </strong>and garnish with the <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
